value.title: Mike Pence breaks silence in op-ed slamming House Dems’ voting reform bill
value.excerpt: Pence made his feelings known in an op-ed published Wednesday by The Daily Signal, a blog run by the conservative Heritage Foundation, where the former VP is a fellow.

value.title: McEnany on Psaki's performance: I didn't have to 'circle back' because Trump gave me access
value.excerpt: Former White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany said Thursday she didn't need to a "ton of circling back" with reporters because of the access afforded her by former President Donald Trump, in a reference to successor Jen Psaki's go-to line when she can't directly answer questions.

value.title: Biden celebrates House passing HR 1, Dems' campaign bill, vows work to 'refine and advance' legislation

value.title: Once omnipresent Kushner now MIA from Trump's political pack
value.excerpt: As Donald Trump plotted his Conservative Political Action Conference appearance last week, and a broader, more-robust plan to return to politics as an omnipresent disruptor, one person was conspicuously absent from the confab.

value.title: First Thing: Biden slams 'Neanderthal' easing of state Covid restrictions

value.title: Trump election fraud investigation in Georgia enters new phase with grand jury set to be seated
value.excerpt: A criminal investigation into former President Donald Trump's attempts to overturn the 2020 election results in Georgia is set to intensify this week, as a grand jury convenes, offering the local district attorney her first shot at seeking subpoenas for records and interviews.

value.title: Biden’s US-Mexico border pullback creating ‘roads for the cartels,’ Arizona sheriff says: report
value.excerpt: The U.S.-Mexico border region in Arizona is becoming less secure since President Biden took office, a sheriff is alleging, according to a report.

value.title: Susan Collins says she’ll back Biden pick Deb Haaland for Interior secretary
value.excerpt: U.S. Sen. Susan Collins, R-Maine, said Wednesday that she will vote to confirm U.S. Rep. Deb Haaland of New Mexico to become secretary of the interior.

value.title: Kimmel warns 'canceling' Dr. Seuss is 'how Trump gets reelected': Cancel culture is 'his path to victory'

value.title: Georgia Gov. Kemp says he would 'absolutely' back Trump 2024, despite Trumps' calls for his resignation
value.excerpt: Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp said he would "absolutely" back Donald Trump in a bid for the presidency in 2024, despite Trump’s recent criticism of the Republican governor.

value.title: Florida Gov. DeSantis slams Biden over pace of school reopenings: 'Pathetic failure of leadership'

value.title: Fact check: Pence echoes Trump's Big Lie in dishonest op-ed on election rules
value.excerpt: In an opinion article published on Wednesday, former Vice President Mike Pence did something he used to do in office: echo a lie from former President Donald Trump in a slightly more sophisticated way.

value.title: House Republican: 'Trump has a responsibility' to tell his supporters 'to stand down' after new threat
value.excerpt: The top Republican on the House Foreign Affairs Committee said Wednesday that Donald Trump has a duty to call off his supporters in light of a potential threat against the US Capitol on Thursday -- less than two months after the January 6 Capitol insurrection incited by the former President.
